                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d926">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.51/503: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-19T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 19, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Your 199, June 17, 8 p.m., last paragraph. You are authorized to proceed in
                    your discretion in the manner indicated.<note n="9" xml:id="d926fn9">For account
                        of Ambassador Weddell’s conference with Franco, see telegram No. 232, June
                        22, 9 p.m., from the Ambassador in Spain, <ref target="#pg_887">p.
                        887</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
